/*
Create a new admin account (manual, no Node script)

1) Open Firebase Console.
2) Go to Authentication > Users.
3) Click Add user, then enter email and password.
4) After creating the user, copy the user UID.
5) Go to Realtime Database > Data.
6) Under users, create a child with Key = <UID>.
7) Set that UID node Value Type to Object.
8) Paste this object as the value:

{
  "uid": "PASTE_UID_HERE",
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "fullName": "Admin Name",
  "role": "admin",
  "createdAt": 1742366400000
}

Required minimum for admin routing in this app:
{
  "role": "admin"
}
*/

/*
Required SDK Version 54  
Required node version 22

Startup commands:
- npm run start:tunnel   (tunnel-only, interactive)
- npm run start:auto     (try tunnel, fallback to LAN)
- npm run start:lan      (LAN only)
*/

/*
Automatic permanent scholar deletion (Auth + DB)

1) Install Firebase CLI once:
  npm install -g firebase-tools

2) Login and verify project:
  firebase login
  firebase use scholr2026

3) Install function dependencies:
  npm run functions:install

4) Deploy function:
  npm run functions:deploy

After deployment, deleting a scholar from Admin Settings will automatically:
- delete Firebase Authentication account (email/password removed)
- delete users/<uid> in Realtime Database
*/